## What was fixed (3 surgical edits to `scripts/test/harness_visual_verify.gd`)

### Fix 1 — Remove pre-V7 FFI name references (Issue 3)
The header comment block was trimmed from 7 lines to 4. The lines naming `get_agent_snapshots`, `get_band_list`, `get_minimap_snapshot`, `get_wall_plans_count` are gone. Only the 3 locked V7 methods are now mentioned.

### Fix 2 — Clean evidence directory at startup (Issue 1)
Added `_clean_evidence_dir()` called in `_init()` immediately after `_ensure_evidence_dir()`. It iterates the evidence directory and calls `DirAccess.remove_absolute()` on every file found, so stale pipeline-injected files (e.g. `godot_output.txt`, partial artefacts from a prior run) are gone before this run writes anything. This guarantees the FINAL count reflects only the 7 files this script produces.

### Fix 3 — Allowlist-based manifest (Issue 2)
Replaced the directory-scan `_write_manifest()` with one driven by a `static var REQUIRED_ARTEFACTS` list of exactly the 6 required non-manifest filenames. The function checks `FileAccess.file_exists()` for each and only emits names that are present. Files not in the allowlist (including any pipeline-side files that survived the startup clean) can never appear in `manifest.txt`.

